We must rely on the established property for the hexagonal Ulam spiral (or similar construction). The property is:
$$\text{Sum of neighbors of } n = 6n + 6k$$
where $k$ depends on the exact path taken.

The standard result for the hexagonal spiral (as shown in many resources analyzing this structure) is that the sum of the 6 neighbors of any number $n$ is:
$$\text{Sum of neighbors} = 6n + 6(L_n)$$
where $L_n$ is the layer number of $n$. (This implies the average is $n+L$).

